CHAPTER 1.
Life is all about intricacies but mine was formed majorly when I was growing up in Ikom, the east of the area on the Cross River and the A4 highway at 5°57′40″N 8°42′39″E as described by Wikipedia, that was where I started to comprehend nature, things and people around me. Back then, we lived in a long straight building with over 15 self contained units particularly designed and built for civil servants. The brown brick wall structure with a chimney attached to each kitchen roof has a tared road in front with an enormous field across, and a large plots of land for cultivation at the backyard.

